Definition.WordDefinition: Involuntarily \In*vol"un*ta*ri*ly\, adv. [From {Involuntary}.] In an involuntary manner; not voluntarily; not intentionally or willingly. [1913 Webster]
involuntarily adv : against your will; "he was involuntarily held against his will" [ant: {voluntarily}]
